sources.title: Dead Men Walk (1943) VAMPIRE
sources.description:
Stars: George Zucco, Mary Carlisle, Dwight Frye
Director: Sam Newfield

The twin of a kindly small-town physician returns from the grave for vengeance against his brother, who secretly killed him because the twin served Satan. Watch for the Dwight Frye, the extremely versatile actor and originator of many memorable characters in the horror genre most notably Renfield from the original Bela Lugosi classic, Dracula.

metadata.Plot: We meet Doctor Lloyd Clayton at the funeral of his twin brother, evil magician Elwyn. Zolarr, Elwyn's hunchbacked servant, accuses Lloyd of Elwyn's murder, but Lloyd claims it was self-defense. Lloyd's niece Gayle and her fiance David soon find that Elwyn's evil influence is still at work.
metadata.Actors: George Zucco, Mary Carlisle, Nedrick Young
